<subSubSection id="C3156577FFD9FF91FCDFFBFCFA90FB77" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB036FCFFD9FF91FCDFFBFCFA90FB77" blockId="5.[827,1443,1058,1203]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FCDFFBFCFC1AFBF3" box="[827,967,1058,1079]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Etymology:</emphasis>
The genus name is the combination of 
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FC85FB9FFC68FB93" box="[865,949,1089,1111]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">hiatus</emphasis>
, opening in Latin, after the broad tracheal spiracle behind the epigastric furrow, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFD9FF91FCDFFBA1FC3BFB50" box="[827,998,1151,1172]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lagonomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FCDFFBA1FC3BFB50" box="[827,998,1151,1172]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Lagonomegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<typeStatus id="54B4885EFFD9FF91FC10FBA1FBFBFB50" box="[1012,1062,1151,1172]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">type</typeStatus>
genus of the family, from Greek -μεγόψ, magnification. The name is masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3156577FFD9FF91FCDFFB03FA95FB35" box="[827,1352,1243,1266]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BB036FCFFD9FF91FCDFFB03FA95FB35" blockId="5.[827,1352,1243,1266]" box="[827,1352,1243,1266]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">
<heading id="D0F88190FFD9FF91FCDFFB03FA95FB35" box="[827,1352,1243,1266]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FCDFFB03FB3EFB35" box="[827,1251,1243,1266]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">
<typeStatus id="54B4885EFFD9FF91FCDFFB03FCADFB36" box="[827,880,1245,1266]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFD9FF91FC35FB02FB3EFB35" authority="Guo &amp; Selden &amp; Ren, 2022" authorityName="Guo &amp; Selden &amp; Ren" authorityYear="2022" box="[977,1251,1243,1265]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Hiatomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FC35FB02FB3EFB35" bold="true" box="[977,1251,1243,1265]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Hiatomegops spinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2485795FFD9FF91FB0EFB02FA95FB35" box="[1258,1352,1244,1265]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3156577FFD9FF91FCDFFAC5FB4CFA48" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB036FCFFD9FF91FCDFFAC5FB4CFA48" blockId="5.[827,1443,1306,1420]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FCDFFAC5FC6FFAF4" box="[827,946,1307,1328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Palpal tibia and tarsus with several dorsal trichobothria; leg metatarsus slightly longer than tarsus; broad tracheal spiracle situated on postgastric area behind epigastric furrow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3156577FFD9FF93FCDFFA6BFDC8FA00" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="406" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB036FCFFD9FF93FCDFFA6BFE5AFCB9" blockId="5.[827,1444,1461,1882]" lastBlockId="7.[163,780,197,1476]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="406" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FCDFFA6BFC71FA0E" box="[827,940,1461,1482]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Remarks:</emphasis>
Finding a fossil spider species in which both males and females have been described is rare. Among 19 reported genera in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFD9FF91FB59FA2CFA40F9CC" authorityName="ESKOV &amp; WUNDERLICH" authorityYear="1995" box="[1213,1437,1522,1544]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lagonomegopidae</taxonomicName>
, only 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFD9FF91FC9EF9CFFAFBF9E2" authority="Wunderlich, 2012" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2012" box="[890,1318,1553,1575]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Archaelagonops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FC9EF9CFFBE3F9E2" box="[890,1086,1553,1574]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Archaelagonops</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFD9FF91FBADF9CFFAFBF9E2" author="Wunderlich J" box="[1097,1318,1553,1575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" pagination="157 - 232" refId="ref12807" refString="Wunderlich J. 2012. On the fossil spider (Araneae) fauna in Cretaceous ambers, with descriptions of new taxa from Myanmar (Burma) and Jordan, and on the relationships of the superfamily Leptonetoidea. Beitrage zur Araneologie 7: 157 - 232." type="journal article" year="2012">Wunderlich, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is known from both male and female specimens. The 
<specimenCount id="9D09FD75FFD9FF91FA93F9EEFC55F9A0" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
specimens, which were subsequently included in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFD9FF91FCBBF9B3FBF8F946" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2012" box="[863,1061,1645,1666]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Archaelagonops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FCBBF9B3FBF8F946" box="[863,1061,1645,1666]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Archaelagonops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(erected on a male specimen originally), lack sufficient evidence to belong in that genus (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFD9FF91FC32F974FB6CF904" author="Wunderlich J" box="[982,1201,1706,1728]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" pagination="157 - 232" refId="ref12807" refString="Wunderlich J. 2012. On the fossil spider (Araneae) fauna in Cretaceous ambers, with descriptions of new taxa from Myanmar (Burma) and Jordan, and on the relationships of the superfamily Leptonetoidea. Beitrage zur Araneologie 7: 157 - 232." type="journal article" year="2012">Wunderlich, 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFD9FF91FB27F974FB20F904" author="Wunderlich J" box="[1219,1277,1706,1728]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" pagination="21 - 408" refId="ref12855" refString="Wunderlich J. 2015. On the evolution and the classification of spiders, the Mesozoic spider faunas, and descriptions of new Cretaceous taxa mainly in amber from Myanmar (Burma) (Arachnida: Araneae). Beitrage zur Araneologie 9: 21 - 408." type="journal article" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
). In general, female spiders are a larger size than conspecific males. Four lagonomegopid species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFD9FF91FB12F936FC55F8DF" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lineaburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beigeli">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FB12F936FC55F8DF" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Lineaburmops beigeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFD9FF91FC73F8D8FA41F8D8" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" box="[919,1436,1798,1820]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lineaburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FC73F8D8FB19F8DF" box="[919,1220,1798,1819]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Lineaburmops maculatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFD9FF91FB28F8D8FA41F8D8" author="Wunderlich J" box="[1228,1436,1798,1820]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" pagination="21 - 408" refId="ref12855" refString="Wunderlich J. 2015. On the evolution and the classification of spiders, the Mesozoic spider faunas, and descriptions of new Cretaceous taxa mainly in amber from Myanmar (Burma) (Arachnida: Araneae). Beitrage zur Araneologie 9: 21 - 408." type="journal article" year="2015">Wunderlich, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFD9FF91FCDFF8FBFAB7F8FF" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" box="[827,1386,1829,1851]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Parviburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipalpus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FCDFF8FBFB59F8FE" box="[827,1156,1829,1850]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Parviburmops brevipalpus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFD9FF91FB6BF8FBFAB7F8FF" author="Wunderlich J" box="[1167,1386,1829,1851]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" pagination="21 - 408" refId="ref12855" refString="Wunderlich J. 2015. On the evolution and the classification of spiders, the Mesozoic spider faunas, and descriptions of new Cretaceous taxa mainly in amber from Myanmar (Burma) (Arachnida: Araneae). Beitrage zur Araneologie 9: 21 - 408." type="journal article" year="2015">Wunderlich, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFD9FF91FCDFF89AFB31F89D" authority="Wunderlich, 2017" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2017" box="[827,1260,1860,1882]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Planimegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFD9FF91FCDFF89AFBFDF89D" box="[827,1056,1860,1881]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="404">Planimegops parvus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFD9FF91FBC2F89AFB31F89D" author="Wunderlich J" box="[1062,1260,1860,1882]" pageId="5" pageNumber="404" pagination="72 - 279" refId="ref12903" refString="Wunderlich J. 2017. New and rare fossil spiders (Araneae) in mid Cretaceous amber from Myanmar (Burma), including the description of new extinct families of the suborders Mesothelae and Opisthothelae, as well as notes on the taxonomy, the evolution and the biogeography of the Mesothelae. Beitrage zur Araneologie 10: 72 - 279." type="journal article" year="2017">Wunderlich, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, comprised only of male specimens, were described as having a similar or smaller size with CNU-ARA-MA2020002, an adult female. CNU-ARA-MA2020002 can be distinguished from them by: carapace without white patch (carapace with distinct white patches in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FDE9FE9EFCD7FE91" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" box="[525,778,320,341]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lineaburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beigeli">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FDE9FE9EFCD7FE91" box="[525,778,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Lineaburmops beigeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FF31FE80FE27FEB7" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" box="[213,506,350,371]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lineaburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FF31FE80FE27FEB7" box="[213,506,350,371]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Lineaburmops maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); carapace much longer than wide (carapace length equal with width in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FF47FE42FE10FE75" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" box="[163,461,412,433]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Parviburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipalpus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FF47FE42FE10FE75" box="[163,461,412,433]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Parviburmops brevipalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); cephalic region of carapace with a pair of anterolateral protrusions next to the inner side of PME (protrusions absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FD9DFE07FF2EFDC9" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Planimegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FD9DFE07FF2EFDC9" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Planimegops parvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). We erected a new genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FDCEFE26FD1CFDC9" box="[554,705,504,525]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Hiatomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FDCEFE26FD1CFDC9" box="[554,705,504,525]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Hiatomegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on CNU-ARA-MA2020002. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FDE1FDC9FD74FDE8" box="[517,681,535,556]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Hiatomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FDE1FDC9FD74FDE8" box="[517,681,535,556]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Hiatomegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the other two lagonomegopid genera (
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FF1BFD8AFE6BFDAD" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2012" box="[255,438,596,617]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lagonoburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FF1BFD8AFE6BFDAD" box="[255,438,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Lagonoburmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FE0AFD8AFD55FDAD" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" box="[494,648,596,617]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Picturmegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FE0AFD8AFD55FDAD" box="[494,648,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Picturmegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) comprised only of female specimens by: body length 2.89 (body length about 8.00 in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FE53FD4FFDA2FD62" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2012" box="[439,639,657,678]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lagonoburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FE53FD4FFDA2FD62" box="[439,639,657,678]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Lagonoburmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); carapace piriform in outline, much longer than wide (carapace distinctly narrowed posteriorly, slightly wider than long in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FEE1FD30FE71FCC7" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" box="[261,428,750,771]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Picturmegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FEE1FD30FE71FCC7" box="[261,428,750,771]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Picturmegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); carapace without a stripe (carapace with distinct stripes in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FDB7FCD2FD27FCE5" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" box="[595,762,780,801]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Picturmegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FDB7FCD2FD27FCE5" box="[595,762,780,801]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Picturmegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); metatarsus of leg I slightly longer than tarsus (metatarsus of leg I about two times longer than tarsus in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FF24FCB6FEAAFCB9" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2012" box="[192,375,872,893]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lagonoburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FF24FCB6FEAAFCB9" box="[192,375,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Lagonoburmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF706674FFDAFF92FF75F950FCF2F8B5" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6599783" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6599783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6599783/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="405" startId="6.[145,225,1678,1700]" targetBox="[191,1379,197,1637]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8BB036FCFFDAFF92FF75F950FCF2F8B5" blockId="6.[145,1425,1678,1905]" pageId="6" pageNumber="405">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDAFF92FF75F950FF21F967" bold="true" box="[145,252,1678,1700]" pageId="6" pageNumber="405">Figure 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDAFF92FEECF950FE63F960" authorityName="Guo &amp; Selden &amp; Ren" authorityYear="2022" box="[264,446,1678,1700]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Scopomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fax">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDAFF92FEECF950FE63F960" box="[264,446,1678,1700]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="405">Scopomegops fax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, holotype CNU-ARA-MA2020001: A, habitus, lateral view; B, schematic drawing of lateral habitus; C, distal part of chelicerae, dorsal view, showing peg teeth; D, tibia and male palp of right pedipalp, dorsal view, showing retrolateral tibial apophysis (arrow); E, tarsus of left leg IV, lateral view, showing trichobothria (asterisks); F, metatarsus of left leg IV, lateral view, showing trichobothria (asterisks) and preening comb (arrow); G, cephalothorax, lateral view, showing eyes and abnormal left leg I; H, tibia of left pedipalp, lateral view, showing trichobothria (asterisks) and retrolateral tibial apophysis (arrow); I, left male palp, retrolateral view; J, left male palp, ventral view; K, 3D CT reconstruction of left male palp, ventral view; L, reconstruction of left male palp, ventral view. Scale bars represent 1 mm (A, B) 0.5 mm (G), 0.2 mm (D, E, F) and 0.1 mm (C, H, I, J, K, L).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB036FCFFDBFF93FF5FFC59FDC8FA00" blockId="7.[163,780,197,1476]" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">
In addition, the 
<typeStatus id="54B4885EFFDBFF93FE4CFC58FDF5FC58" box="[424,552,902,924]" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">holotypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FDBBFC59FDCBFC7E" authority="Penney, 2004" authorityName="Penney" authorityYear="2004" class="Arachnida" family="Grandoculidae" genus="Grandoculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chemahawinensis">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FDBBFC59FEAEFC7E" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Grandoculus chemahawinensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDBFF93FE98FC7BFDCBFC7E" author="Penney D" box="[380,534,933,954]" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" pagination="579 - 584" refId="ref11781" refString="Penney D. 2004. Cretaceous Canadian amber spider and the palpimanoidean nature of lagonomegopids. Acta Paleontologica Polonica 49: 579 - 584." type="journal article" year="2004">Penney, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
,? 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FDD5FC78FCD7FC7F" box="[561,778,934,955]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lagonomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cor">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FDD5FC78FCD7FC7F" box="[561,778,934,955]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Lagonomegops cor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDBFF93FF47FC1AFDC4FC1D" author="Perez-De La Fuente R &amp; Saupe EE &amp; Selden PA" box="[163,537,964,986]" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" pagination="531 - 553" refId="ref11839" refString="Perez-De La Fuente R, Saupe EE, Selden PA. 2013. New lagonomegopid spiders (Araneae: † Lagonomegopidae) from Early Cretaceous Spanish amber. Journal of Systematic Palaeontology 11: 531 - 553." type="journal article" year="2013">
Pérez-de la Fuente 
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FE77FC1AFE12FC1D" box="[403,463,964,985]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">et al.</emphasis>
, 2013
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FDCDFC1AFF2CFC3C" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Soplaogonomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unzuei">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FDCDFC1AFF2CFC3C" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Soplaogonomegops unzuei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDBFF93FF1DFC3CFDBFFC33" author="Perez-De La Fuente R &amp; Saupe EE &amp; Selden PA" box="[249,610,994,1016]" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" pagination="531 - 553" refId="ref11839" refString="Perez-De La Fuente R, Saupe EE, Selden PA. 2013. New lagonomegopid spiders (Araneae: † Lagonomegopidae) from Early Cretaceous Spanish amber. Journal of Systematic Palaeontology 11: 531 - 553." type="journal article" year="2013">
Pérez-de la Fuente 
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FE05FC3DFDC6FC33" box="[481,539,994,1016]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">et al.</emphasis>
, 2013
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FD95FC3DFEE4FBD3" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Spinomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aragonensis">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FD95FC3DFEE4FBD3" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Spinomegops aragonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDBFF93FEA0FBDFFD0CFBD2" author="Perez-De La Fuente R &amp; Saupe EE &amp; Selden PA" box="[324,721,1025,1047]" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" pagination="531 - 553" refId="ref11839" refString="Perez-De La Fuente R, Saupe EE, Selden PA. 2013. New lagonomegopid spiders (Araneae: † Lagonomegopidae) from Early Cretaceous Spanish amber. Journal of Systematic Palaeontology 11: 531 - 553." type="journal article" year="2013">
Pérez-de la Fuente 
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FDA6FBDCFD5EFBD2" box="[578,643,1025,1047]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">et al.</emphasis>
, 2013
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FF47FBFEFE7DFBF1" box="[163,416,1056,1077]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Spinomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arcanus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FF47FBFEFE7DFBF1" box="[163,416,1056,1077]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Spinomegops arcanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDBFF93FE4CFBFEFCD6FBF1" author="Perez-De La Fuente R &amp; Saupe EE &amp; Selden PA" box="[424,779,1056,1078]" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" pagination="531 - 553" refId="ref11839" refString="Perez-De La Fuente R, Saupe EE, Selden PA. 2013. New lagonomegopid spiders (Araneae: † Lagonomegopidae) from Early Cretaceous Spanish amber. Journal of Systematic Palaeontology 11: 531 - 553." type="journal article" year="2013">
Pérez-de la Fuente 
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FD6FFBFEFD18FBF1" box="[651,709,1056,1077]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">et al.</emphasis>
, 2013
</bibRefCitation>
were identified as ‘juvenile or adult female’ (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDBFF93FD56FBE1FF07FBB6" author="Penney D" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" pagination="579 - 584" refId="ref11781" refString="Penney D. 2004. Cretaceous Canadian amber spider and the palpimanoidean nature of lagonomegopids. Acta Paleontologica Polonica 49: 579 - 584." type="journal article" year="2004">Penney, 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDBFF93FF01FB83FDEAFBB6" author="Perez-De La Fuente R &amp; Saupe EE &amp; Selden PA" box="[229,567,1117,1139]" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" pagination="531 - 553" refId="ref11839" refString="Perez-De La Fuente R, Saupe EE, Selden PA. 2013. New lagonomegopid spiders (Araneae: † Lagonomegopidae) from Early Cretaceous Spanish amber. Journal of Systematic Palaeontology 11: 531 - 553." type="journal article" year="2013">
Pérez-de la Fuente 
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FE5AFB80FE28FBB6" box="[446,501,1117,1139]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">et al.</emphasis>
, 2013
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FDAEFB80FD03FBB7" box="[586,734,1118,1139]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Hiatomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FDAEFB80FD03FBB7" box="[586,734,1118,1139]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Hiatomegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily separated from these by: carapace piriform in outline, without neck (carapace heart-shaped when viewed from above in? 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FE58FB64FD44FB0B" box="[444,665,1210,1231]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lagonomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cor">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FE58FB64FD44FB0B" box="[444,665,1210,1231]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Lagonomegops cor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; cephalic region constricted in a neck, with narrowest point medially in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FED7FB28FDB7FAC8" box="[307,618,1270,1292]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Soplaogonomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unzuei">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FED7FB28FDB7FAC8" box="[307,618,1270,1292]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Soplaogonomegops unzuei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), fovea small oval, deeply depressed (fovea absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FD96FACBFEEBFA8D" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Spinomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aragonensis">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FD96FACBFEEBFA8D" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Spinomegops aragonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FE9CFAEAFD5BFA8D" box="[376,646,1332,1353]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Spinomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arcanus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FE9CFAEAFD5BFA8D" box="[376,646,1332,1353]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Spinomegops arcanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), leg I not enlarged, metatarsus and tarsus without scopulae (leg I distinctly longer and more robust than the others, metatarsus and tarsus with scopulae hairs in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDBFF93FF47FA70FDD8FA07" authorityName="Penney" authorityYear="2004" box="[163,517,1454,1475]" class="Arachnida" family="Grandoculidae" genus="Grandoculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chemahawinensis">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDBFF93FF47FA70FDD8FA07" box="[163,517,1454,1475]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="406">Grandoculus chemahawinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
